text: Etowah County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 103,436. The county seat is Gadsden. The name is from a Cherokee word meaning "edible tree". It is the smallest county in Alabama, but one of the most densely populated. == References == Category:Alabama counties Category:1866 establishments in Alabama
title: Etowah County, Alabama
